    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Building technique using short firewood-sized logs set in piles perpendicular to the length of walls and held in place by mortar or wooden frames.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042441/Noble, Wood, Brick and Stone (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Técnica constructiva que usa troncos de tamaño de leña puestos en pilas perpendiculares al largo de las paredes y mantenidas en su sitio por argamasa o armazones de madera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bouwtechniek waarbij korte blokken hout, ter grootte van brandhout, loodrecht op de langste zijde van muren worden gestapeld, en op hun plaats worden gehouden door specie of houten raamwerken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
